th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>to be a robber,</b> ὁτιὴ ’πιώρκεις ἡρπακώς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 428, compare “Pl.” 372\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἁρπάζειν βλέπει looks <b>thievish,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Ἐπιτρέποντες” 181:\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i> (or <i>middle</i>), ἐκ χερῶν ἁρπάζομαι I <b>have</b> her <b>torn</b> from my arms, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 661. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>seize hastily, snatch up,</b> λᾶαν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.445; δόρυ 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 624; τὰ ὅπλα 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 6.1.8\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἁ. τινὰ μέσον <b>seize</b> him by the waist, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.107\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; λίθος ἥτις τὸν σίδηρον ἁρπάζει, of the magnet, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Steril.” 243: with _genitive_ of the part seized, ἁ. τινὰ τένοντος ποδός 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 400: with _genitive_ _partitive_, ἁ. τούτων ἐνέτραγον 4th c.BC: Timocles Comicus 16.7: _absolutely_, ἀπογεύονται ἁρπάζοντες \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>greedily,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 354b\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Sacr.” 3. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>seize, overpower, overmaster,</b> γλῶσσαν ἁ. φόβος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 259\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>seize, occupy</b> a post, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 4.6.11\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἁρπάσαι πεῖραν <b>seize</b> an opportunity of attacking, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 2; ἁ. τὸν καιρόν 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Philopoemen” 15\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>snap up,</b> ὥσπερ εὕρημα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 6.30. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>seize, adopt</b> a legend, of an author, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.156. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>grasp with the senses,</b> ὀσμαὶ -όμεναι ταῖς ὀσφρήσεσιν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.647e. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> <b>captivate, ravish,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Jdt.16.9, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Antonius” 28. \">LXX+1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__7</b></Level3> <b>draw up</b> by means of a vacuum, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.AD: Simplicius Philosophus “in Aristotelis Physica commentaria - Comm. in Arist. Graeca” 647.28. \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>plunder,</b> πόλεις, τὰ ἐκ τῶν οἰκιῶν, τὴν Ἑλλάδα, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.5, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 7.2.5, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 8.55, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0726","accentedUnicode":"ἁρπάζω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0138","matchingForm":"αἱρέω","stepTransliteration":"haireō","gloss":"to choose","_zh_tw_Gloss":"選擇","_es_Gloss":"escoger","_zh_Gloss":"选择"},{"strongNumber":"G0727","matchingForm":"ἅρπαξ","stepTransliteration":"harpax","gloss":"rapacious","_zh_tw_Gloss":"勒索","_es_Gloss":"rapaz","_zh_Gloss":"勒索"},{"strongNumber":"G1283","matchingForm":"διαρπάζω","stepTransliteration":"diarpazō","gloss":"to rob","